    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-04T13:57:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-04T13:57:00-05:00" n="1361"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1361">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">774.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/8–3054:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1361<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Egypt</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-04T14:57:00-04:00"
                            >September 4, 1954—2:57 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>382. Joint State–<gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss> Message. Re <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>s 268. and 271. Magnitude of Egyptian
                    program considered September 2 with <persName corresp="#p_SHE1"
                        >Stassen</persName>, who is prepared authorize program $20 million now and
                    likewise prepared consider up to further $20 million for economic assistance,
                    but for this purpose needs persuasive documentation in terms <pb facs="0599"
                        n="2301" xml:id="pg_2301"/> uses <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> and
                    Public Law 480—Agricultural Trade Development and Assistance Act<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1361fn1">See <ref target="#d1350fn4">footnote 4, Document
                            1350</ref>.</note>—funds and justification of anticipated obligations
                    and expenditures of proposed projects in form discussed <gloss
                        target="#t_Usfoto1">Usfoto</gloss> 100.<note n="2" xml:id="d1361fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> Submit telegraphic summary.</p>
                <p>Regret cannot yet authorize disclosure possibility $40 million figure to <gloss
                        target="#t_GOE1">GOE</gloss> at this time, but you should encourage
                    presentation project material up to this limit.</p>
                <p>Need for justification requested above intensified by reduction by Congress funds
                    requested for Development Assistance, major cuts elsewhere in <gloss
                        target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> Program and urgent claims unforeseen when
                    budget presented—examples Greece and Pakistan.</p>
                <p>Embassy <gloss target="#t_USOM1">USOM</gloss> should inter alia appraise total
                    agricultural surplus products that might move to Egypt from <gloss
                        target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> funds, pursuant Section 402 of Act, whose local
                    currency sales proceeds could be made available by US provide project local
                    currency requirements. Such use should be consistent with Section 104 of <gloss
                        target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> Appropriation Act<note n="3" xml:id="d1361fn3"
                        >See <ref target="#d1359fn1">footnote 1, Document 1359</ref>.</note> which
                    requires that local currency be used for same purposes as dollars where from
                    granted. Congressional presentation <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> included
                    explanation that $12 million of $20 million requested for Egypt would be in form
                    Surplus Agricultural Commodities. Whatever aid can come from Public Law 480
                    resources may have to take form of agricultural goods in excess $12 million
                    financed by <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> funds.</p>
                <p>Embassy <gloss target="#t_USOM1">USOM</gloss> should also consider and comment on
                    effect loan requirements in <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss> legislation.
                        <gloss target="#t_USG1">USG</gloss> hopes to have loan provisions worked out
                    at early date in form which will not impair capacity borrow from <gloss
                        target="#t_IBRD1">IBRD</gloss> and other institutions.<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d1361fn4">Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName>
                        responded to this final paragraph of telegram 382 on Sept. 9 in telegram
                        318, not printed. <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Caffery</persName> stressed
                        that Egypt needed aid in the form of grants, not loans, and concluded with
                        the thought that American loan assistance would not be regarded as real aid
                        by the Egyptians. (774.5 <gloss target="#t_MSP1">MSP</gloss>/9–954)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                            </hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
